'''Rico Peter''' (born 13 September 1983) is a Swiss [[bobsleigh|bobsledder]].<ref name="fibtprofile">[http://www.fibt.com/bobsleigh/athletes.html?athl_id=130115 FIBT Profile]</ref>

Peter competed at the [[2014 Winter Olympics]] for Switzerland. He teamed with brakeman [[Juerg Egger]] in the Switzerland-2 sled in the [[Bobsleigh at the 2014 Winter Olympics – Two-man|two-man]] event, finishing tenth.<ref name="sportsrefprofile">{{cite web |title=Sports Reference Profile|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/pe/rico-peter-1.html}}</ref><ref name="sochi2014profile">{{cite web|title=Sochi2014.com profile |date=March 19, 2014 |url=http://www.sochi2014.com/en/athlete-rico-peter |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140319074240/http://www.sochi2014.com/en/athlete-rico-peter |archivedate=March 19, 2014 }}</ref>

As of April 2014, his best showing at the [[FIBT World Championships|World Championships]] is 6th, in [[FIBT World Championships 2013|2013]] four-man event.<ref name=fibtprofile/>

Peter made his [[Bobsleigh World Cup|World Cup]] debut in December 2011. As of April 2014, his best finish is 5th, in [[2013–14 Bobsleigh World Cup|2013-14]] at [[Konigssee]].<ref name=fibtprofile/>

